<TITLE> Col Farooq aide remanded </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Faridpur, June 28 (bdnews24.com)A Faridpur Court on Sunday granted police three days to question BK Hamidul Haque, 55, a close aide of retired colonel Farooqur Rahman, the self-confessed killer of independence hero Sheikh Mujibur Rahman. Hamidul was arrested on Friday night. Ashraful Islam, chief judicial magistrate of Faridpur, granted three days after hearing police's appeal to remand him for seven days. Kotowali police chief Nur-e-Alam said Bulbul was planning subversive activities with the members of banned Freedom Party and Islamist outfit Jammatul Mujahideen Bangladesh. bdne
